# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 10 (Enterprise Accessibility)

Spec: `docs/12_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_10_ACCESSIBILITY.md`

## Rules

- Prefer semantic HTML (`main`, `nav`, `button`, `label`, `dialog`, `th scope`) over ARIA.
- Use `focusRing` from `src/lib/ui/tokens.ts` on custom interactive controls.
- Use `src/lib/a11y/focus.ts` (`trapFocus`, `restoreFocus`, `focusFirstElement`) for non-native overlays.
- Native `<dialog showModal()>` must set `aria-modal="true"` and stable labelled headings (`useId`).
- Never rely on placeholder text as the only form label.
- Decorative icons/images must be hidden from assistive technology; meaningful ones need names.
- Status meaning must not rely on color alone.
- Do not remove focus outlines or redesign layouts for accessibility work.
- Never weaken auth, RBAC, RLS, Paddle billing, API contracts, or SEO behaviour.

## This chapter

- Do not commit, push, or deploy from Chapter 10 work.
